@progressive
subtitle: It is crucial that we secure our ties with the dovish Democrats.
on-arrival: consumer_dove += 1; worker_dove += 1; establishment_dissent += 2; democrat_relation += 5

It takes some convincing to get the McGovernites to agree to attend, but eventually he is pursuaded, though attends solely as an observer for the time being. An orderly convention is organized, though quite modest due to the haste of preparation and lack of resources. Eugene McCarthy is greeted by modest applause and takes a seat as the convention proceeds. Speeches are made, calling for an end to the Vietnam War, support for Civil Rights, and other such standard progressive promises. By the end of it, McCarthy is officially nominated in a vote by our attending delegates, and ties built with the remaining McGovernites in the Democratic Party, should we attempt to secure a Democratic ally.

- @continue_progressive: Intriguing.

