@mobe
subtitle: We cannot forget the other major group behind the Chicago protests.
on-arrival: dependence -= 2; unemployed_dove += 5; youth_dove += 2; unemployed_democrat -= 2

The Mobe is happy to help organize and participate in our convention, and quickly organize that of their protestors who remain in the city in support of Eugene McCarthy. When he arrives at the convention he is greeted by a large crowd of protestors who cheer him on. He is greeted by Rennie Davis, one of the leaders of the Chicago office of the Mobe, and led inside into the convention. The convention begins and resounding speeches are made by multiple Mobe speakers as well as our delegates, and by the end of it Eugene McCarthy is officially nominated for president.

- @continue_mobe: Intriguing.

